    • Class com.vangav.backend.push_notifications.apple.AppleNotification extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -8584619114492996393L

      • Serialized Fields

        • deviceToken

          java.lang.String deviceToken
          MANDATORY deviceToken (e.g.: an iPhone's token) - i.e.: a device's ID for the push notification to reach to the right device

        • badgeNumber

          int badgeNumber
          OPTIONAL overrides the number in the red circle on an app's icon that identifies the number of new events (notifications, messages, photos, etc ...)

        • sound

          java.lang.String sound
          OPTIONAL sound is used to override the device's default notification sound possibly a silent notification

        • alertBody

          java.lang.String alertBody
          OPTIONAL the notification's message (e.g.: the one that appears on the iPhone's lock screen) Can be left empty for silent notifications. Silent notifications are used for events like marking seen messages in real-time without having to pop-it-up in the form of a regular notification, so that it reaches the app without distracting the person using the device.

        • customProperties

          java.util.HashMap<K,V> customProperties
          OPTIONAL customProperties doesn't show to the person using the device Custom properties are used by the app. e.g.: ID of the user who created the notification's event, ID of the photo to add the comment to, etc ...
